That’s not to say that great news for the stock market never matters for regular Americans.
To be alive in America is to be assaulted by endless high-decibel blather about the critical importance of the stock market.
To understand this, you have to look at some basic facts about what the stock market is, and what it isn’t.
Here on Earth, the stock market would have punished any company that took such a big risk with an uncertain payoff.
And there are pernicious effects of our stock market love affair that are even more subtle.